# Project Rules

## Environment Files Access
- You have permission to read and edit .env, .env.local, .env.development, .env.production files
- Help configure environment variables when needed
- Never expose secret values in responses to the user, just confirm they are set

## Project Context
- This is a Next.js 16 project called "Shotsy"
- Uses Clerk for authentication
- Uses Polar.sh for payments
- Uses Prisma with PostgreSQL
- Uses OpenRouter API for AI (Gemini model)
- Uses Upstash Redis for rate limiting

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript
- Use CSS Modules for styling
- Follow existing code patterns

